o.d: One of the most popular beaches lined with shacks and street shopping. Come here for thrilling watersports and restaurants offering authentic Goan cuisine.
Home to the famous beaches of North Goa. Visit attractions like Fort Aguada, Museum of Goa and Chapora Fort. Party at vibrant nightclubs, bars and casinos.
Indulge in watersports at one of the longest and peaceful beaches of Goa. Enjoy flavoursome food and drinks at the shacks and beach restaurants.
Most lively and touristy beach area in North Goa. Enjoy sundowner parties with Bollywood music. Stop by the flea market to collect souvenirs, relish local delicacies and drinks.
Famed for its beach parties, nightlife and hippie culture, Anjuna offers budget accommodation. Visit the flea market to collect souvenirs and ride to offbeat corners on rental scooters.
Home to the city’s best casinos, ancient churches and architectural marvels, Panjim offers a wide range of hotels from budget to luxury.
A beautiful coastal village with powder white sand beach and coconut trees along the coastline. Unwind at the beach shacks, pubs and bars or indulge in watersports here.
